                <h2>What Does Microneedling Do for Hyperpigmentation?</h2>

                <p>We see thousands of patients at DenceSpot Clinic struggling violently with melasma, sunspots, or Post-Inflammatory Hyperpigmentation (the dark brown/red marks left agonizingly behind long after a pimple has vanished).</p>

                <p>The dark marks occur because a localized cluster of melanocytes—the pigment-producing cells—misfired in a panic and dumped high volumes of dark melanin pigment directly into the lower levels of the epidermis.</p>

                <p>Microneedling accelerates your cell turnover rate at an explosive speed. The needles physically agitate and break up the heavy, stagnant clumps of dark melanin trapped beneath the surface. As the skin rapidly regenerates and pushes the old, dead cells completely to the uppermost layer, the shattered melanin chunks are rapidly shed from the face entirely. For patients strictly focused on dark discoloration who may be terrified of lasers, microneedling combined with specialized skin lightening infusions severely out-performs heavy uncalibrated lasers in terms of absolute safety for Indian skin tones. Always confirm the details in local <a href="../carbon-facial-in-gurgaon.php">carbon facial treatment</a> alternative comparisons as well.</p>

